Optional W^X / JIT for 9front amd64 — wxallow gate + SG_EXEC per-segment opt-in.
Diffs are against stock 9front /sys/src/9 (Plan 9 `diff` normal format: `<` = old,
`>` = new). See README.md. Apply by hand (4 small edits) on the box, then rebuild
in /sys/src/9/pc64 and install the kernel to /n/9fat/9pc64 (the 9fat partition is
what 9boot loads — NOT /amd64/9pc64).

===== /sys/src/9/port/portdat.h =====
413a414
> 	SG_EXEC		= 04000,	/* Executable data (W^X opt-in, gated by wxallow) */

(added inside the "Segment types" enum, right after `SG_NOEXEC = 02000`)

===== /sys/src/9/port/segment.c =====
10a11
> int wxallow;			/* W^X gate; set from plan9.ini in confinit() */

(file-scope global, just before `static Physseg physseg[10]`)

823a825,828
>
> 	/* W^X opt-in: SG_EXEC honored only when the wxallow gate is set. */
> 	if((attr & SG_EXEC) != 0 && wxallow == 0)
> 		attr &= ~SG_EXEC;

(in segattach(), right after `attr &= ~(SG_TYPE | SG_CACHED | SG_DEVICE);`)

===== /sys/src/9/port/fault.c =====
252c252
< 	if((s->type & SG_NOEXEC) != 0 || s->flushme == 0)
---
> 	if(((s->type & SG_NOEXEC) != 0 || s->flushme == 0) && (s->type & SG_EXEC) == 0)
282c282
< 	if((attr & SG_NOEXEC) != 0 || s->flushme == 0)
---
> 	if(((attr & SG_NOEXEC) != 0 || s->flushme == 0) && (s->type & SG_EXEC) == 0)

(both are the `mmuphys |= PTENOEXEC;` guards: don't mark NX if the segment is SG_EXEC)

